{"type":"message","id":"1a568e72","parentId":"b285842a","timestamp":"2026-03-19T11:35:22.804Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The context monitor is reporting that context usage is at 78%, which exceeds the 60% threshold. I should create a log entry and potentially update memory. Let me check if MEMORY-LITE.md exists and its word count.\n\nActually, looking at the AGENTS.md instructions, I should be proactive but also stay quiet instead of creating vague or noisy proactivity. The context usage is 78% - this is getting high. I should note this in the session state or heartbeat file so that future checks know to potentially alert the user.\n\nLet me check the memory directory and the heartbeat state to understand the pattern of checks being done.","thinkingSignature":"56ecd19cebcbd449e3ec54fe1fe269cf65d3cdcca35858f345efc3f3213fb7b9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ci24bva6e9yu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -Command \"if (Test-Path '$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\MEMORY-LITE.md') { (Get-Content '$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\MEMORY-LITE.md' -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue -TotalCount 500) }\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1368,"output":231,"cacheRead":37011,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38610,"cost":{"input":0.0005472000000000001,"output":0.0003465,"cacheRead":0.00148044,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0023741400000000003}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773920116698}}
