{"type":"message","id":"8a1e66d4","parentId":"89fcc61b","timestamp":"2026-03-19T11:35:47.326Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. I've updated the heartbeat state and today's memory file. Context usage is at 78% and climbing. Based on the rate of increase (~9% per ~4 hours extrapolated), it could hit 85% in about 3-4 hours. \n\nThe system should automatically create a new session when it hits 85%. I've done what was needed - tracked the state. I should NOT send a message to the user proactively at this time (it's 19:35, and while not late night, the usage is not yet at the critical 85% threshold where auto-action would be taken). The cron will continue to monitor every 30 minutes.\n\nLet me just confirm the update was written correctly.","thinkingSignature":"7ef92468c373b4a8624e13c4de615ca81efe015f2bd7e91db7512dcc1b1248cf"},{"type":"text","text":"Context monitor: **78%** (156,819/200,000 tokens) — ⚠️ exceeding 60% threshold\n\nContext has been climbing steadily today:\n- 15:45 → 67%\n- 19:00 → 76%  \n- 19:35 → 78%\n\nAt the current rate (~9% per 4 hours), it could hit the 85% auto-trigger threshold in roughly 3-4 hours. The system will automatically spawn a fresh session with memory loaded when that happens.\n\nI've updated `heartbeat-state.json` and `memory/2026-03-19.md` with the current reading. No user notification needed yet — the automation handles it."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2630,"output":290,"cacheRead":37011,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39931,"cost":{"input":0.001052,"output":0.000435,"cacheRead":0.00148044,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00296744}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773920139788}}
